	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Microchip uses Netbeans as the base for their MPLAB X IDE, which should be cross-platform, but IIRC it doesn't come with a compiler, so you'll have to download that separately (they do have free compilers available, it's just a separate download, and different downloads for different chip families, so be sure to get the right one). Honestly, Microchip kind of (i.e. really really REALLY) sucks in the user friendliness department. They have code examples, including ones for their USB stack, but there are multiple options of compilers, and it's never clear which compiler the example is designed for. I finally got my hands on one of those chips, but so far I haven't even gotten it to enumerate. USB is a huge PitA <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
