	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: GB Flasher PCB's</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No, that just means that they used the extra pins on the QFP-44 package to move the ICSP pins off of the GPIO's.  On the DIP package, the ICSP pins are shared with GPIO's and therefore &quot;use up&quot; those pins (RB6/RB7).  However, if you're careful with your design, you can share the pins without any issue.  The DIP package absolutely does have ICSP capabilities, it just doesn't get its own dedicated pins for it.  Look at the bottom of Table 1 on page 5 for PGC and PGD (aka ICSPCLK and ICSPDAT).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

